# Movie Recommender System

A content-based movie recommendation web application built with Python, Streamlit, and machine learning. Select any movie and instantly get 5 similar recommendations — complete with posters fetched live from TMDB.

![Movie Recommender System](Predict.png)

---

## Live Demo

> Run locally using Streamlit — see setup instructions below.

---

## Features

- **Content-Based Filtering** — Recommends movies based on genres, cast, crew, keywords, and overview
- **Live Movie Posters** — Fetches real-time posters via the TMDB API
- **5 Smart Recommendations** — Displays the top 5 most similar movies for any selection
- **Fast & Interactive UI** — Built with Streamlit for a clean, responsive experience
- **Robust Error Handling** — Graceful fallback if poster or API is unavailable

---

## How It Works

```
User selects a movie
        ↓
Fetch its index from the movies dataset
        ↓
Compute cosine similarity against all other movies
        ↓
Sort by similarity score → Pick top 5
        ↓
Fetch posters from TMDB API
        ↓
Display recommendations with titles & posters
```

### ML Pipeline (Notebook)

1. **Data Loading** — Merged `tmdb_5000_movies.csv` and `tmdb_5000_credits.csv`
2. **Feature Engineering** — Extracted genres, cast (top 3), director, and keywords
3. **Text Processing** — Applied stemming and combined features into a single "tags" column
4. **Vectorization** — Used `CountVectorizer` (5000 features) to convert tags to vectors
5. **Similarity Matrix** — Computed cosine similarity across all movie pairs
6. **Serialization** — Saved `movies.pkl` and `similarity.pkl` for the Streamlit app

---

## Project Structure

```
movie-recommender-system/
│
├── app.py                                  # Streamlit web application
├── movie-recommender-system-checkpoint.ipynb  # ML model training notebook
│
├── movies.pkl                              # Serialized movies dataframe
├── similarity.pkl                          # Precomputed cosine similarity matrix
│
├── tmdb_5000_movies.csv                    # Raw movies dataset
├── tmdb_5000_credits.csv                   # Raw credits dataset
│
├── Predict.png                             # App screenshot
└── README.md                               # Project documentation
```

---

## Tech Stack

| Technology | Purpose |
|------------|---------|
| Python 3.x | Core language |
| Pandas | Data manipulation |
| Scikit-learn | Vectorization & cosine similarity |
| NLTK | Text stemming |
| Streamlit | Web application UI |
| Pickle | Model serialization |
| TMDB API | Live movie poster fetching |
| Requests | HTTP calls to TMDB |

---

## Installation & Setup

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/movie-recommender-system.git
cd movie-recommender-system
```

### 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install pandas streamlit scikit-learn nltk requests
```

### 3. Run the App

```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

The app will open at `http://localhost:8501` in your browser.

> **Note:** The `movies.pkl` and `similarity.pkl` files must be present in the root directory. They are already included in this repository.

---

## TMDB API Key

This project uses the [TMDB API](https://www.themoviedb.org/documentation/api) to fetch movie posters.

To use your own key:
1. Register at [themoviedb.org](https://www.themoviedb.org/)
2. Go to **Settings → API** and generate a key
3. Replace the key in `app.py`:

```python
url = f"https://api.themoviedb.org/3/movie/{movie_id}?api_key=YOUR_API_KEY_HERE"
```

---

## Dataset

- **Source:** [TMDB 5000 Movie Dataset on Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/tmdb/tmdb-movie-metadata)
- **Size:** ~5,000 movies
- **Files used:**
  - `tmdb_5000_movies.csv` — Movie metadata (genres, overview, keywords, etc.)
  - `tmdb_5000_credits.csv` — Cast and crew information

